    <item>
      <title>What is Double Extortion Ransomware?</title>
      <link>https://ghariib.ir/posts/what-is-double-extortion-ransomware/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 22 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ghariib.ir/posts/what-is-double-extortion-ransomware/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://cybermaniacs.com/hubfs/Understanding%20the%20Menace%20of%20Ransomware.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;What is Double Extortion Ransomware?&#34; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Double extortion&lt;/strong&gt; is an advanced ransomware tactic where attackers not only encrypt a victim&amp;rsquo;s data to demand a ransom for decryption but also steal the data and threaten to release or sell it publicly if the ransom isn’t paid. Talk about salt in a wound, this one is the worst. &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://track.hubspot.com/__ptq.gif?a=20922849&amp;amp;k=14&amp;amp;r=https%3A%2F%2Fcybermaniacs.com%2Fcm-blog%2Fwhat-is-double-extortion-ransomware&amp;amp;bu=https%253A%252F%252Fcybermaniacs.com%252Fcm-blog&amp;amp;bvt=rss&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Go to Source&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>&lt;div&gt;Enhanced Phishing Training: Dealing with Today&#39;s Threats&lt;/div&gt;</title>
